children.subject: Where is the application to be a UGSI for fall 2017 located

history.content: The application of UGSI for fall 17 says that if English is not my native language (which is my case, I am an international student) then I have to submit the Language Proficiency Questionnaire; however, the link doesn't work. Also, it asks for my grade on some spoken English tests but I never took any of them. So my question is that if I cannot submit that questionnaire what I should do? Will my application even be valid? Also, do I have to take any of those spoken tests? Thanks in advance for any clarifications!
